ilies a better deal…How the Other Half Banks is well researched and clearly written…The bankers who fully understand the system are heavily invested in it. Books like this are written for the rest of us.” —Nancy Folbre, New York Times Book Review “How the Other Half Banks tells an important story, one in which we have allowed the profit motives of banks to trump the public interest.” —Lisa J. Servon, American Prospect  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aBanks and bankingxSocial aspectsxUnited States. 0aBanks and bankingxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aCheck cashing servicesxUnited States. 0aCheck cashing serviceszUnited States. 0aFinancial services industryxUnited States. 0aFinancial services industryzUnited States. 0aPostal savings banksxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aPostal savings bankszUnited States. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Banks & Banking.2bisacsh  aAmerican Banking industry.  aConsumer Financial Protection Bureau.  aDodd-Frank Act.  aHamilton.  aJefferson.  abanking reform.  acheck-cashing services.  ademocratization of credit.  afringe banks.  apayday lenders.  apayday loan.  apostal banking.  apostal savings system.  apublic option financial services.  aunequal credit.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311066590140uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/978067449542540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674495425423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674495425/original  a978-3-11-066590-1  Harvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  